# gen72: Italian conversational content words added to lexicon.pl as stopwords
# no longer trigger the word-reflecting fallback ("Hmm, I don't know about X").
# Instead they get the classic or generic fallback. Bilingual ratchet:
# the same stopword mechanism works for both languages.
> dimmi niente
< I don't understand that yet.
> ancora niente
< I didn't quite catch that. What would you like to know?
> ehi tranquillo
< Hi there!
> questo e un casino
< I don't understand that yet.
> parliamo di formaggio
< I'm not sure I followed. Can you say it another way?
